KERNEL DESIGN
  d=64, BM=16 query rows/block, BN=16 key rows/tile. 1 block = 1 warp (32 thd).
  grid.x = N/16. Each block streams all N/16 key tiles with online softmax.
  QK^T : 4 wmma K-tiles (d=64) -> S[16x16] f32 acc -> scale -> wmma.store.d to
         SHARED s_tile (f32). mma.row.col (A=Q row, B=K col = K^T).
  softmax: lanes 0..15 own one S row each; running max+sum in shared; P written
         as f16 to shared p_tile; running O tile rescaled by c in shared.
  P.V  : load P (shared, row f16) once; 4 wmma over V (global, row f16) -> 4 O
         partials -> added into shared o_tile (mma.row.row).
  finalize: o_tile[i]/l[i] -> f16 -> ONE global store (the only HBM write).

